cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Presburger-definable sets and their representation using automata, which is a topic closely related to logic in computer science.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper discusses efficient algorithms for manipulating Presburger-definable sets.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with automata and their representation of sets.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the construction of a Presburger-formula, which is a topic related to programming languages.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem of deciding if a FDVA represents a Presburger-definable set and provides a polynomial time algorithm for the same.
